{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/automate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2", "time": 1683006764.102321, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/automate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Automate Your Excel Reporting with Python! | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Automate Your (Boring!) Excel Reporting with Python!", "description": "Automate your Excel reporting with Python using Pandas and Openpyxl to create separate Excel workbooks, with formatting, and beautiful graphs."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-step-by-step-guide-to-pandas-pivot-tables-e0641d0c6c70", "anchor_text": "Pandas Pivot Table tutorial", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/automate-these-3-boring-excel-tasks-with-python-666b4ded101b", "anchor_text": "Automate These 3 (Boring!!) Excel Tasks with Python!", "paragraph_index": 8}], "all_paragraphs": ["Excel is everywhere. There\u2019s no escaping it, even with powerful tools like Python at your disposal.", "And that\u2019s ok! Your boss and your colleagues still need easy ways to access important data.", "But that doesn\u2019t mean that you can\u2019t make your work with Excel easier by using Python, all without touching Excel!", "You know those Excel reports you do on a monthly, weekly (daily?) basis? The ones where you do the same thing four or five times for different clients?", "Let Python do that for you!", "Let\u2019s take a quick look at what we\u2019ll be automating! We\u2019re going to be using data from my Pandas Pivot Table tutorial (which I really recommend checking out!).", "The data format matches what you might expect to get from a corporate database with client sales on it.", "We\u2019re going to be breaking that data out by region and creating two summary tables, with formatting and with charts. All without ever touching Excel!", "We\u2019re going to be relying on Pandas and Openpyxl. I covered Openpyxl quite a bit in my story Automate These 3 (Boring!!) Excel Tasks with Python! which gives you a good introduction to how it operates.", "We\u2019re going to be using two libraries:", "Let\u2019s load our data and take a quick look at what we\u2019re working with!", "As I mentioned, the data is meant to resemble what you might get from a corporate database system.", "Here, we\u2019re using pandas to read an Excel file, parsing the Date column as dates.", "Let\u2019s create the summary table we will want in our final reports.", "To sample, this let\u2019s create a pivot table just for the East region to try out our code.", "Now that we have our pivot table, let\u2019s load it into an Excel file.", "For this, we\u2019ll use pandas to load it:", "Let\u2019s take a quick look as to what we\u2019re doing:", "Pandas is good for getting the data to Excel. Now that it\u2019s there, let\u2019s pretty it up a bit and add some visualizations.", "There\u2019s quite a bit going on here. Let\u2019s explore it in more detail!", "In Section 5, we\u2019re loading the workbook and worksheets into separate objects that Openpyxl can handle.", "Section 6 has a bit more going on:", "In Section 7, we add our bar chart:", "This is what our sheet looks like now:", "While this is already handy, doing this for one region only saves us a little bit of time. Let\u2019s do this for all regions with a for-loop.", "Let\u2019s take a closer look here:", "In Section 8, we create a list that has all the unique values of the different regions we want to cover.", "In Section 9, we repeat our earlier code in a for-loop:", "The nice thing about Python is how scaleable it makes repetitive tasks.", "Imagine getting this file daily and having to create these workbooks every day. You\u2019ve just saved yourself a good chunk of time every day!", "We learned quite a bit in this short tutorial! We transformed a workbook into a set of pivot tables, exported those into separate workbooks, and applied formatting and graphs to each workbook!", "Give yourself a pat on the back!", "If you\u2019re interested in more content like this, check out my other stories about Excel, such as the one below:", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F233dd61fb0f2&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fautomate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fautomate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fautomate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fautomate-excel-reporting-with-python-233dd61fb0f2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------g